1
00:00:09,320 --> 00:00:11,640
-(ALARMS BEEPING)
-Data breach.

2
00:00:11,720 --> 00:00:14,320
There's been a data breach
in the core drives. We are compromised.

3
00:00:14,400 --> 00:00:16,800
I repeat, we are compromised.

4
00:00:19,480 --> 00:00:22,280
-Hello. Nice to see you again.
-Who the hell are you?

5
00:00:22,360 --> 00:00:24,360
(TUTS) How quickly they forget.

6
00:00:24,440 --> 00:00:26,960
I'm the Doctor.
And this is the Inforarium,

7
00:00:27,040 --> 00:00:29,920
the greatest source of
illicit information in recorded history.

8
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:32,640
Which is fine, your business,
but you've been selling it

9
00:00:32,720 --> 00:00:36,000
to the Daleks, to the Cybermen
and the Sontarans. That's just naughty.

10
00:00:36,120 --> 00:00:38,200
-(CONSOLE BLEEPS)
-If you're trying to raise the alarm,

11
00:00:38,280 --> 00:00:41,680
I wouldn't bother. I'm not really here.
I'm a recorded message.

12
00:00:41,760 --> 00:00:44,400
-You're a what?
-A recorded message.

13
00:00:44,480 --> 00:00:47,000
-Then how can you be replying to me?
-You're very predictable. Thing is

14
00:00:47,080 --> 00:00:49,000
I'm on a bit of a mission
at the moment.

15
00:00:49,080 --> 00:00:51,320
I've been deleting every piece
of information about myself

16
00:00:51,400 --> 00:00:53,480
-from every database in the universe.
-Why?

17
00:00:53,560 --> 00:00:56,840
-I want to be alone.
-Well, you can't delete it from here.

18
00:00:56,920 --> 00:01:00,200
All our data is quantum-stored.
It exists at 12 levels of reality...

19
00:01:00,280 --> 00:01:04,280
And now you're probably boasting
about "12 levels of reality”. Boring!

20
00:01:04,360 --> 00:01:07,600
You're right.
I can't delete any of your data.

21
00:01:07,680 --> 00:01:10,040
-But I can memory-proof it.
-Memory-what?

22
00:01:10,120 --> 00:01:13,000
Any information from this facility
concerning me

23
00:01:13,080 --> 00:01:15,240
will be forgotten
seconds after it is learned.

24
00:01:15,320 --> 00:01:17,120
Clever trick.
Learned it from the Silence.

25
00:01:17,200 --> 00:01:19,880
-(LAUGHS) That's impossible.
-Anything about me, the Doctor,

26
00:01:19,960 --> 00:01:23,280
the last of the Time Lords,
will just disappear from your mind

27
00:01:23,360 --> 00:01:25,840
-like it was never there.
-It can't be done.

28
00:01:28,040 --> 00:01:31,000
You know what?
Better check your drives.

29
00:01:32,320 --> 00:01:34,320
(ALARMS BEEPING)

30
00:01:34,400 --> 00:01:36,960
Data breach. There's been a data breach
in the core drives.

31
00:01:37,040 --> 00:01:40,520
We are compromised.
I repeat, we are compromised.

32
00:01:40,600 --> 00:01:42,400
(HOLOGRAM PROJECTOR TURNS ON)

33
00:01:42,480 --> 00:01:45,160
-Hello. Nice to see you again.
-Who the hell are you?

34
00:01:45,240 --> 00:01:47,360
(TUTS) How quickly they forget.

35
00:01:47,440 --> 00:01:49,920
I'm the Doctor.
And this is the Inforarium...

